Detailed Description

Stores all the strings used by one map.

The strings are accessed by one StringVector with pointers to all the strings. This vector also constains the total number of strings in this object. The actual strings are stored in the memory in one of these two alternatives:

  • The first stings are stored in one memory-area, theStrings.
  • The strings that have been added later are stored in small buffers with one string in each.

bool OldItemNames::exchangeString (  uint32  strIdx,
const char *  newName
)  [private]
 

Exchange a string in the stringtable with a new one.

Warning:
Make absolutely sure that you know what you are doing when you call this method! Make sure that all items that has this name would like it to be exchanged with the new one.
Note:
Only strings that are not blocked could be exchanged!
Parameters:
strIdx The stringindex to be exchanged with a new string.
newName The new name.
Returns:
True if the exchanging was succesful, otherwise false (could happen if the name was in the blocked strings).
